The following components are derived from Ent's design and API:
- Schema definition API (velox.Schema, velox.Field, velox.Edge, velox.Mixin, velox.Index)
- Privacy layer (privacy.Allow, privacy.Deny, privacy.Skip, privacy.FilterFunc)
- Hook and interceptor middleware pattern (velox.Hook, velox.Interceptor, velox.Traverser)
- Query builder API patterns (Where, Limit, Offset, Order, Select, GroupBy)
- Mutation type design (field getters/setters, edge add/remove/clear)
- Error type hierarchy (NotFoundError, NotSingularError, ConstraintError, ValidationError)
- Feature flag system (FeaturePrivacy, FeatureIntercept, FeatureUpsert, etc.)
- Schema field builders (field.String, field.Int, field.Enum, etc.)
- Edge definition builders (edge.To, edge.From, edge.Unique, edge.Through)

Velox differs from Ent in the following architectural areas:
- Code generation uses Jennifer (github.com/dave/jennifer) instead of text/template
- Per-entity sub-package layout instead of flat package
- Pure Go SQLite driver (modernc.org/sqlite) instead of CGO-based sqlite3
- Runtime registry pattern for cross-package entity dispatch
